sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as kserve-webhook-server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as kserve-controller-manager<br/>ServiceAccount Auth
    participant StorageInit as storage-initializer<br/>Init Container
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Istio IngressGateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant VirtualService as VirtualService<br/>Istio Routing
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Eventing as Knative Eventing Broker<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Eventing: Flow 1: Model Deployment

    User->>APIServer: Create InferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OAuth)
    APIServer->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate InferenceService<br/>mTLS (API Server client cert)
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Validation response
    APIServer-->>User: CR created

    Controller->>APIServer: Watch InferenceService CRs<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    APIServer-->>Controller: InferenceService created event

    Controller->>APIServer: Create Deployment/KnativeService<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    APIServer-->>Controller: Resources created

    Note over StorageInit,S3: Model Download (Init Container)

    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS IAM/GCP SA/Azure credentials
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model files

    Note over Client,Eventing: Flow 2: Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    Gateway->>VirtualService: Route request<br/>mTLS (optional via Istio)
    VirtualService->>Predictor: Forward to predictor<br/>mTLS (optional via Istio)
    Predictor->>Predictor: Run inference

    alt Logging enabled
        Predictor->>Eventing: Send request/response logs<br/>HTTP (TLS via Istio optional)
    end

    Predictor-->>VirtualService: Prediction result (JSON)
    VirtualService-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Eventing: Flow 3: InferenceGraph Multi-Model Pipeline

    participant Router as Router Service<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Preprocessor as Preprocessor InferenceService<br/>8000/TCP
    participant MainPredictor as Main Predictor InferenceService<br/>8000/TCP
    participant Postprocessor as Postprocessor InferenceService<br/>8000/TCP

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/graph:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    Gateway->>Router: Route to InferenceGraph<br/>mTLS (optional via Istio)

    Router->>Preprocessor: Step 1: Preprocess<br/>Bearer Token (propagated)
    Preprocessor-->>Router: Preprocessed data

    Router->>MainPredictor: Step 2: Predict<br/>Bearer Token (propagated)
    MainPredictor-->>Router: Raw prediction

    Router->>Postprocessor: Step 3: Postprocess<br/>Bearer Token (propagated)
    Postprocessor-->>Router: Final result

    Router-->>Gateway: Pipeline result
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Eventing: Flow 4: LLM Disaggregated Inference

    participant LLMRouter as LLM Router Service<br/>8000/TCP
    participant Scheduler as LLM Scheduler<br/>9003/TCP gRPC
    participant PrefillWorker as Prefill Worker<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/gRPC
    participant DecodeWorker as Decode Worker<br/>8001/TCP HTTP/gRPC

    Client->>Gateway: POST /openai/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
    Gateway->>LLMRouter: Route to LLM service<br/>mTLS (optional via Istio)
    LLMRouter->>Scheduler: Schedule request<br/>gRPC, mTLS (optional)

    Scheduler->>PrefillWorker: Send to prefill worker<br/>gRPC, mTLS (optional)
    PrefillWorker-->>Scheduler: KV cache generated

    Scheduler->>DecodeWorker: Send to decode worker<br/>gRPC, mTLS (optional)
    DecodeWorker-->>Scheduler: Generated tokens (streaming)

    Scheduler-->>LLMRouter: Streaming response
    LLMRouter-->>Gateway: Streaming response
    Gateway-->>Client: Streaming JSON (SSE)

    Note over Client,Eventing: Flow 5: Local Model Cache

    participant LocalModelMgr as localmodel-manager
    participant DownloadJob as Download Job Pod
    participant LocalPV as Local PersistentVolume<br/>Node Disk
    participant InferencePod as InferenceService Pod

    LocalModelMgr->>APIServer: Create Download Job<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    APIServer-->>LocalModelMgr: Job created

    DownloadJob->>S3: Download model to local PV<br/>Storage credentials
    S3-->>DownloadJob: Model files
    DownloadJob->>LocalPV: Write to PV<br/>Filesystem (fsGroup: 1000)

    InferencePod->>LocalPV: Mount local PV<br/>Direct filesystem access
    LocalPV-->>InferencePod: Model files (fast access)
